. The following year she was captured by the Burgundians and sold to the English, and a year later she was burned at the stake for witchcraft at the age of 18 or 19. Her story has captured the imagination of many writers, and she is variously portrayed as a national and political hero, a model of apolitical straightforwardness and honesty, and a religious heroine. She was canonized in  1920 . More recent influences have included the American film actress  Joan Crawford  (  1908–77 , born  Lucille le Sueur ), the British actress  Joan Collins  (  b. 1933 ), the American comedienne  Joan Rivers  (  b. 1933 ), and the West Indian pop singer  Joan Armatrading  (  b. 1950 )."],"variants":[{"name":"John","meanings":["Greek: the Lord gave graciously; whom Jehovah gave; whom Jehovah bestowed."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"Joan was born about 1153, in Cirencester, Gloucestershire, England, United Kingdom. She had at least 2 sons with Walleran de Chichester. She died in 1194, at the age of 42."},"et":{"abt. 1153–1194":"umbes 1153–1194","1154–1194":"1154–1194","1184–Male":"1184–Surnud","1188–1220":"1188–1220","1153–1194":"1153–1194","Abt 1188":"umbes 1188","1188":"1188","1220":"1220","1154":"1154","1153":"1153","1184":"1184","1194":"1194","abt. 1153":"umbes 1153","Chichester, Sussex, England":"Chichester, Sussex, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Cirencester, Gloucestershire, England, United Kingdom":"Cirencester, Gloucestershire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Chichester, Sussex, England, United Kingdom":"Chichester, Sussex, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"abt. 1153–1194":"noin 1153–1194","1154–1194":"1154–1194","1184–Male":"1184–Kuollut","1188–1220":"1188–1220","1153–1194":"1153–1194","Abt 1188":"noin 1188","1188":"1188","1220":"1220","1154":"1154","1153":"1153","1184":"1184","1194":"1194","abt. 1153":"noin 1153","Chichester, Sussex, England":"Chichester, Sussex, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Cirencester, Gloucestershire, England, United Kingdom":"Cirencester, Gloucestershire, Engla